<title>|xue and his wives</title>
<summary>This is a story about |xue and his wives (!nanni says that he saw |xue, his  house and child while !nanni was with the Herero). |xue resembles a lizard one day, a |ou (a small buck, probably a steenbok) the next, and a little tsema and a ||ha and a python (â‰ ni), all on different days. When |xue dies he resembles the |ou (and has horns). As |xue lies there dead his wives see him and come and pick him up and carry him to the house. The elder (or &apos;greater&apos;) wife makes a fire to cook the kid, and puts his body on the fire. |xue calls out, objecting to being put on the fire. The second wife takes |xue to her house and covers him with a kaross. He bites it and becomes a kid again. The second wife kills him and puts him in a cooking pot, shutting him in and covering him. He becomes an ant and bites his second wife. His wife crushes his ant&apos;s head and throws |xue down on the ground.</summary><comments>1) p.9298v: !nanni heard this from his paternal grandfather (Karu); |xue was a !kun, 2) p.9303v: a race of people called the |ka kue who are like the |nani; they kill the Makoba as well as !kun; they use bows but not guns and come from the same country as the Shimbari and the |nani, 3) p.9306v: the !kun name for &apos;thinking-strings&apos;, 4) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-4</comments><date>8 February 1880 (started)</date><storypages>9299-9310, 9316-9324</storypages><category>Transformation</category><category>Relations with others</category><author>!nanni (XI)</author><keyword><kw>!nanni</kw><subkw>saw |xue when he was with the Herero</subkw></keyword>
